es are sensitive to the\nstructural and chemical changes induced by thermal annealing. Furthermore,\nusing mid-IR spectroscopy, we have successfully identified the production of\nradiolytic daughter molecules as a result of 1 keV electron irradiation and the\ninfluence of temperature over this chemistry. Such results are directly\napplicable to studies on the chemistry of interstellar ices, comets, and icy\nlunar objects and may also be useful as reference data for forthcoming\nobservational missions.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Sun, 6 Mar 2022 01:33:42 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-03-08"}
